news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP extends deadline for revised PG norms to September 21
news.para: BBMP had initially set a Sept 15 deadline, warning that failure to comply would draw action under Sections 307 and 308 of the 2020 BBMP Act. The guidelines include a requirement of 70 sqft per person and a 90-day retention period for CCTV footage — measures strongly opposed by the PG Owners' Welfare Development Association.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body revises terms for auction of 13 plots
news.para: The AMC has revised its tender for the auction of 13 plots in the city, which was initially announced on Aug 22. The new terms stipulate that buyers pay 10% of the amount within 10 days and the remaining 90% within 90 days.

news.title: Ahmedabad: SRFDCL engages with global builders ahead of auction for riverfront plots
news.para: ​​This strategic push was detailed in the annual audit report presented to the SRFDCL board on Sep 6, just before the Request for Proposal (RFP) was announced for the auction of two prime plots. The riverfront project, spanning 204.91 hectares, is set to make a significant impact.

news.title: Punjab urban development bodies collects Rs 2,945 crore via e-auction of land parcels
news.para: In the official release, Chief Minister Bhagwant Mann said the e-auction got a massive response from the public especially by those who either wanted to own a residential plot or had plans to start a commercial establishment.

news.title: South Africa's Naspers gets CCI clearance to buy minority stake in Vastu Housing Finance
news.para: "The proposed transaction involves the acquisition of less than 10 per cent equity shareholding (on a fully-diluted basis) in Vastu Housing Finance Corporation Ltd (VHFCL) by Naspers Ventures," the regulator said in a release.

news.title: Arkade Developers IPO gets subscribed 16.20 times on day two of bidding
news.para: The portion for non-institutional investors attracted 28.26 times subscription while the category for Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) got subscribed 19.99 times. The quota for Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) fetched 44 per cent subscription.

news.title: Bajaj Housing Finance shares surge 10% upper circuit after market debut
news.para: On the NSE, shares of the firm surged 10 per cent to Rs 181.50 -- the highest trading permissible limit for the day. The company's market valuation climbed Rs 13,733.12 crore to Rs 1,51,139.21 crore. The stock has surged 159.28 per cent from its issue price of Rs 70.

news.title: Indore: MSME department to start fresh online land allotment in 2025
news.para: "We are overhauling the entire system and portal for a seamless and transparent system of land allocation. Allocation of land through the portal is temporarily suspended and we are anticipating to start with the new system by early 2025. In the new system, we are planning to synchronize all basic and advanced procedures for an enhanced interface," said MSME commissioner Dr Navneet Mohan Kothari.

news.title: NCDRC directs Namakkal civic body to pay compensation for inadequate service
news.para: In May 2021, the NMC was sent a letter of approval, instructing it to collect the delimitation and development fees and issue the delimitation order. The woman’s husband, Karthikeyan, repeatedly met corporation officials to process the same but did not receive proper response.

news.title: Indore civic body seals three shops for commercial use of basements
news.para: Acting on the directives issued by collector Asheesh Singh, a joint team comprising officials from the district administration and Indore Municipal Corporation sealed the basements of four buildings that were found to be exploiting parking spaces for commercial activities.

news.title: Gaurs Group to launch its IPO in next 18 months: Manoj Gaur, CMD
news.para: ​​ Byoued by the successful launch of its luxury housing project in Ghaziabad clocking Rs 3,100 crore sales in three days, Gaur said the company has set a target to expand its business of development of housing projects across the Delhi-NCR market.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Indirapuram residents protest against pollution from dumping yard
news.para: The dumpyard, spread over 10 acres, is on a vacant land behind the Khoda police station. Residents alleged that over 100 trucks dispose of their waste at this site daily, resulting in tonnes of garbage accumulating in the yard.

news.title: Hyderabad: Dharani panel suggests third-party audit of portal
news.para: It also said the maintenance of the Dharani portal should be given to govt agencies such as National Informatics Centre (NIC), Centre for Good Governance (CGG), or TSOnline, as the govt data should be protected and address privacy concerns. As of now, the Dharani portal is being managed by a private agency.

news.title: Prayagraj civic body initiates QR code facility for depositing house tax
news.para: With the new system, residents will not only have the convenience of depositing house tax from their residences, but will also get an additional 2.5% rebate in house tax.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP seals illegal flats in Palam Vihar after HC notice
news.para: The building, located at House No 913, had been previously sealed due to unauthorised construction, but the owner unlawfully broke the seal and resumed activities.

news.title: Nexus Venture Partners sells stake in India Shelter Finance for Rs 482 crore
news.para: US-based Nexus Venture Partners, through its affiliates Nexus Ventures III and Nexus Opportunity Fund II Ltd, offloaded 64 lakh shares, amounting to a 5.97 per cent stake in India Shelter Finance Corporation through two separate bulk deals on the BSE.

news.title: Bombay HC slams SRA for delayed Kanjur village slum survey
news.para: Justices Mahesh Sonak and Kamal Khata on Sept 11 directed SRA to file a detailed affidavit explaining the reasons why no survey has been conducted despite HC's Nov 18, 2022, order to finish it within six months.

news.title: Delhi development body extends final payment deadline for Dwarka flats
news.para: The new deadline for making the 25% payment of the total value is now Sept 30, Earlier, it was Aug 31. The authority said the decision was in response to buyers' requests as they needed more time to arrange for money. The deadline was pushed back also because finishing work is going on in the flats.

news.title: MahaRERA grants relief to over 70 Ruparel Skygreens buyers over delayed possession
news.para: The promoter had failed to deliver possession to the allottees — including those who had booked the flats under the subvention schem, and the construction link plan scheme — by the dates agreed and the MahaRERA completion date of Dec 2021.
